description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stamford Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Nurse (newly qualified and experienced)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are exciting and progressive new pathways and innovations happening at Tameside and Glossop Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have various shift patterns to offer to suit you. Full time and part time, Monday - Friday, Weekends only and Nights only.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity to work within our Stamford unit at Tameside and Glossop Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust and we are looking for Band 5 Nurses (experienced and newly qualified).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Unit is supported by a GP 8 hours per day, 7 days a week and out of hours we have medical provision provided by the Go to Doc service. In addition to this we have a number of in reach services available from Digital Health, IV Community Nurses, Active Tameside, Mental Health, Dieticians, Podiatry, EOL services and District Nursing Teams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want our patients to get up and dressed and stay as active as they are able whilst on the unit to enable them to maintain their strength and mobility. We support our patients in maintaining their independence and choice, working as a collaborative team we plan, deliver and promote safe and quality discharges. The team in the Stamford Unit consists on Occupational Therapist, Physiotherapist, Social Workers, Integrated Urgent Care Team and District Nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tameside and Glossop Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust is a fantastic Trust to work for; in return for your care and commitment to this speciality we will actively support staff education and development. We offer excellent development programmes at Band 5 level including clinical skills, mentorship training and link nurse roles, and for newly qualified nurses, we have an outstanding preceptorship programme to ensure that you are well supported to get your career off to the best start and to enable you to achieve your potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note interviews will be arranged upon receipt of applications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are a newly registered nurse we will pay for your NMC registration upon qualification for the first year&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Joanne Hopkins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0161 922 5820&lt;/p&gt;
